Our Story
Seeta is a 38-year-old married woman from a small village of Murshidabad, West Bengal. She has a family of 5 members and a monthly household income of INR 12000.

She and her husband are engaged in the animal husbandry business. They purchase a cattle, harvest milk at their home and sell the milk to the nearby dairy. She has one son and a daughter. The income is barely enough to cover the family expenses. She plans to purchase more cattle in order to expand her business.
